    "showcase the evolution of supervised and deep learning models in detecting smart contract vulnerabilities from 2018 to 2023, respectively.",
    "Supervised models were initially introduced in 2019, exhibiting a rising trend in usage for vulnerability detection until 2023.",
    "On the other hand, deep learning models were introduced in 2018, displaying a similar upward trajectory in usage for vulnerability detection until 2022.",
    "However, Fig. 6.",
    "indicates a declining trend in the utilization of deep learning for vulnerability detection in 2023."
